      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUATRO MOTH (5) resumes from a spell of three-and-a-half months after closing off last campaign with a solid second after racing wide from a back row draw at Kilmore. She is two from two when fresh and should be ready to go again off a trial win. KING SAINT (7) continued his impressive run of recent efforts last start when runner-up at this circuit and distance, beaten 3.5 metres. Scored back-to-back wins at Kilmore and Melton prior. Has to contend with a wide draw but he is going well. OKANUI BEACH (10) cops a tough draw but has yet to miss a place in four fresh attempts and was readied with two trials, winning the latest. Best form measures up favourably so just needs a bit of luck to go his way. LINE DANCE (2) has drawn to advantage and is going well, following a win at this circuit and distance with a last-start second at Shepparton.",
